node.title: Baby boy tests positive for COVID-19 in Hobart quarantine after flight from Melbourne
node.alt: An Asian woman in black coat wheels two big suitcases outside the arrivals door of an airport
node.description: Both mother and son were tested for COVID-19 while in quarantine in Hobart, with Public Health Tasmania informed of the infant's positive result on Sunday.
node.content: ["An 18-month-old boy who travelled from Melbourne to Hobart with his mother last Thursday has tested positive to COVID-19.", "The toddler flew into the state with his mother who did not have a\u00a0valid Good to Go travel pass.", "They were stopped at Hobart Airport and taken to hotel quarantine.", "Both were tested for COVID-19\u00a0while in quarantine, and Public Health Tasmania was informed of the infant's positive result on Sunday.", "\"The two were transferred to Hobart's Community Case Management Facility this evening,\" Tasmania's Deputy Director of Public Health Dr Julie Graham said in a statement on Sunday.", "\"The child is well.", "Hobart's airport has now been listed as a low-risk exposure site between 8:25pm and 9:50pm on Thursday, November 18.", "People who were at the airport at that time have been\u00a0asked to monitor themselves and to get tested if symptoms develop."]
